<p>I want to covert C++ string to <code>NSString</code> to use in iOS app. </p>  <p>But sometimes the result is nil for C++ string with strange suffix format.</p>  <p><em>For example: a C++ string "but in fact it turned out to be you!$\211/" will produce nil after convert to <code>NSString</code>.</em> </p>  <pre><code>mainFile.open(filePath, std::ios::binary); mainFile.seekg(current_offset); char buffer[size];  mainFile.read(buffer, sizeof buffer); string tempString = string(buffer) NSString *testString = [NSString stringWithCString:tempString.c_str() encoding:NSUTF8StringEncoding]; </code></pre>  <p>When <code>cout &lt;&lt; tempString</code> I still read the string content with a strange code suffix, but it produces nil after convert to <code>NSString</code></p>  <p><strong>Anyone know how to fix this?</strong></p>